IT Budget




Diamond Offshore Drilling, Inc. is a contract drilling company that provides global services to the energy industry. It is also involved in deepwater drilling and owns a fleet of offshore rigs across the globe, which comprises 30 semisubmersibles, 13 jack-ups,… MoreDiamond Offshore Drilling, Inc. is a contract drilling company that provides global services to the energy industry. It is also involved in deepwater drilling and owns a fleet of offshore rigs across the globe, which comprises 30 semisubmersibles, 13 jack-ups, and one drillship. Headquartered in Houston, TX, Diamond Offshore Drilling also maintains five regional offices, one of which is in New Orleans, LA, with two in Europe and one each in South America and Australia.
Diamond Offshore Drilling, Inc. is a contract drilling company that provides global services to the energy industry. It is also involved in deepwater drilling and owns a fleet of offshore rigs across the globe, which comprises 30 semisubmersibles, 13 jack-ups,… MoreDiamond Offshore Drilling, Inc. is a contract drilling company that provides global services to the energy industry. It is also involved in deepwater drilling and owns a fleet of offshore rigs across the globe, which comprises 30 semisubmersibles, 13 jack-ups, and one drillship. Headquartered in Houston, TX, Diamond Offshore Drilling also maintains five regional offices, one of which is in New Orleans, LA, with two in Europe and one each in South America and Australia.

The IT department of Diamond Offshore Drilling, Inc. is based in the Houston, TX Headquarters where its primary data center is located. Following the departure of the CIO in early 2012, IT operations are lead by the COO and CFO until a replacement can be found. Managers are responsible for IT functions such as Computer Systems, Network Operations, and Telecommunications. There is also an IT manager who handles Compliance.

The company has partnered with Oracle and utilizes their software packages for its human resources, financial, accounting, administrative, and database development functions. The IT department of Diamond Offshore Drilling, Inc. operates independently from its parent company, Loews Corporation.

Loews Corporation is maintained as a separate profile within the Rainking database.





